    "Being an unsupervised framework, this approach has been widely utilized for biomedical image analysis to address data limitation and class imbalance issues.",
    "A detailed discussion and technical papers can be found in Kazeminia et al. (2020), Yi et al. (2019).",
    "In conditional image synthesis, GANs consider some prior conditional information together with z to generate new synthetic images.",
    "This type of image synthesis faces training challenges of GANs during the image-to-image translation tasks.",
